A vintage-style technical illustration depicting two distinct data architectures side by side: on the left, a warm amber-toned lotus flower with layered petals containing nested compartments representing hierarchical document storage; on the right, a cool steel-blue grid of interconnected cylindrical containers arranged in rigid rows and columns representing relational tables. Between them, delicate copper pipes and mechanical gears attempt to bridge the gap, some successfully connecting while others hang incomplete. The scene is rendered like a 1950s engineering diagram with subtle sepia tones, crosshatching textures, and aged paper quality. Small worker figures in period clothing tend to the machinery at various connection points. The overall composition suggests the complexity and craftsmanship required when two fundamentally different data philosophies must coexist.
